Class AbstractSkippingIteration<T,E extends Exception>

java.lang.Object
  com.complexible.common.collect.AbstractSkippingIteration<T,E>
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.complexible.common.base.Closeable, SkippingIteration<T,E>, com.complexible.common.iterations.Iteration<T,E>
public abstract class AbstractSkippingIteration<T,E extends Exception>
extends Object
implements SkippingIteration<T,E>

Similar to AbstractIteration but handles skipping correctly. Implementations supporting skipping (in the sense of implementing SkippingIteration should inherit from this class rather than from AbstractIteration).

Since:
2.2.2
Author:
Pavel Klinov

public final T skipTo(T theElement)

Description copied from interface: SkippingIteration
Returns the element which is equal or greater to theElement based on the ordering of the elements in the underlying data source, i.e., for two elements A, B s.t. B comes after A during iteration, theComparator should return A <= B.
